<br>
But at level 57 (or on various robes and items), the component is a Tiny Jade Inlaid Coffin, at 40-50pp each, and they are stackable.<br>
<br>
When I look at the time it takes to grab a couple of corpses versus Summoning them for an immediate rez, especially on a time-intensive raid, I wonder why the coffins aren't used more often.  As I understood it, the raid fees cover such contengencies.<br>
<br>
I would suggest that some of the fees that have been collected be used to buy a stack of coffins, and they be used when they would save time - just to see how long a stack would last for KCoG.  I think there are a lot of raid leaders who would be very surprised at just how much time this would save - especially when you have just a couple of corpses down in the pits at Vox, or when a Fear break goes wrong and the whole party got zapped by imps.<br>
<br>
Just another rambling from your friendly neighborhood necro. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nerissagoldenrose>NerissaGoldenrose</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.nxane.com/nerissa/purpleNotes10x10.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Dragon Raid Liason</span><br>  Posts: 189<br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/8/03 11:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=403.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.nxane.com/nerissa/yellowRose1b.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Summoning corpses</span><hr size=1> It's a thought, but for the most part summoning is a last resort because the raid fees don't cover enough coffins for everyone in the case of a wipe-out, and when we don't wipe out the corpses are mostly very easy to get.  (barring a couple of tough spots in the pits for Vox)  I tend to prefer to get as many as we can without summoning, and save the money for times when we absolutely CANNOT get the corpses any other way.<br>
<br>
The other problem is that you aren't always available <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   If we are stuck with a lower-level necro or SK to summon the corpses, then not only are we out more cash, but the coffins are heavy and not stackable, and that nice stack of tiny coffins isn't doing much good.  If we don't have the coffins with us, the call has to be made whether it will take more time to get the corpse(s) or to run out for coffins, and I don't think many of our leaders have enough experience to make a very good guess on that.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying I won't try it... as soon as I get my bank organized a bit to make more room, I plan to go buy a stack to have ready for the next dragon raid, and we'll see how it goes.  <br>
<br>
