<br>
As to the cost:  Again, I think it may be worth it just to summon when there are fewer corpses - as long as the person is in zone, this is done in seconds, with no risk whatsoever.  When time is a big factor (often the case on dragon raids), summoning 3 people will basically eat the fees for one group on a dragon raid, or 2 people for a planes raid.  And if the coffins are already bought and kept on hand by the RL, it's much easier to say just summon him and let's get going.<br>
<br>
And even if I'm not at the raid, you may want to try giving me a tell.  If I'm not on at all, just try to contact any necro over level 57 (or in a guild that does velious content regularly) - most necros will do summons for a raid pretty cheap, especially if the coffins are provided.<br>
<br>
